moves.name: Fake Out
moves.desc: Has a 100% chance to make the target flinch. Fails unless it is the user's first turn on the field.
moves.shortDesc: Hits first. First turn out only. 100% flinch chance.

moves.name: Nuzzle
moves.desc: Has a 100% chance to paralyze the target.
moves.shortDesc: 100% chance to paralyze the target.

moves.name: Thunderbolt
moves.desc: Has a 10% chance to paralyze the target.
moves.shortDesc: 10% chance to paralyze the target.

moves.name: Electroweb
moves.desc: Has a 100% chance to lower the target's Speed by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 100% chance to lower the foe(s) Speed by 1.

moves.name: Endeavor
moves.desc: Deals damage to the target equal to (target's current HP - user's current HP). The target is unaffected if its current HP is less than or equal to the user's current HP.
moves.shortDesc: Lowers the target's HP to the user's HP.

moves.name: Volt Switch
moves.desc: If this move is successful and the user has not fainted, the user switches out even if it is trapped and is replaced immediately by a selected party member. The user does not switch out if there are no unfainted party members, or if the target switched out using an Eject Button or through the effect of the Emergency Exit or Wimp Out Abilities.
moves.shortDesc: User switches out after damaging the target.

moves.name: Upper Hand
moves.desc: Has a 100% chance to make the target flinch. Fails if the target did not select a priority move for use this turn, or if the target moves before the user.
moves.shortDesc: 100% flinch. Fails unless target using priority.

moves.name: Protect
moves.desc: The user is protected from most attacks made by other Pokemon during this turn. This move has a 1/X chance of being successful, where X starts at 1 and triples each time this move is successfully used. X resets to 1 if this move fails, if the user's last move used is not Baneful Bunker, Burning Bulwark, Detect, Endure, King's Shield, Max Guard, Obstruct, Protect, Quick Guard, Silk Trap, Spiky Shield, or Wide Guard, or if it was one of those moves and the user's protection was broken. Fails if the user moves last this turn.
moves.shortDesc: Prevents moves from affecting the user this turn.

moves.name: Helping Hand
moves.desc: The power of the target's attack this turn is multiplied by 1.5 (this effect is stackable). Fails if there is no ally adjacent to the user or if the ally already moved this turn, but does not fail if the ally is using a two-turn move.
moves.shortDesc: One adjacent ally's move power is 1.5x this turn.

moves.name: Surf
moves.desc: Damage doubles if the target is using Dive.
moves.shortDesc: Hits adjacent Pokemon. Double damage on Dive.

moves.name: Feint
moves.desc: If this move is successful, it breaks through the target's Baneful Bunker, Detect, King's Shield, Protect, or Spiky Shield for this turn, allowing other Pokemon to attack the target normally. If the target's side is protected by Crafty Shield, Mat Block, Quick Guard, or Wide Guard, that protection is also broken for this turn and other Pokemon may attack the target's side normally.
moves.shortDesc: Nullifies Detect, Protect, and Quick/Wide Guard.

moves.name: Thunder
moves.desc: Has a 30% chance to paralyze the target. This move can hit a target using Bounce, Fly, or Sky Drop, or is under the effect of Sky Drop. If the weather is Primordial Sea or Rain Dance, this move does not check accuracy. If the weather is Desolate Land or Sunny Day, this move's accuracy is 50%. If this move is used against a Pokemon holding Utility Umbrella, this move's accuracy remains at 70%.
moves.shortDesc: 30% chance to paralyze. Can't miss in rain.

moves.name: Alluring Voice
moves.desc: Has a 100% chance to confuse the target if it had a stat stage raised this turn.
moves.shortDesc: 100% confuse target that had a stat rise this turn.

moves.name: Thunder Wave
moves.desc: Paralyzes the target. This move does not ignore type immunity.
moves.shortDesc: Paralyzes the target.

moves.name: Tera Blast
moves.desc: If the user is Terastallized, this move becomes a physical attack if the user's Attack is greater than its Special Attack, including stat stage changes, and this move's type becomes the same as the user's Tera Type. In addition, if the user's Tera Type is Stellar, this move has 100 power, is super effective against Terastallized targets and neutral against other targets, and lowers the user's Attack and Special Attack by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: If Terastallized: Phys. if Atk > SpA, type = Tera.

moves.name: Reflect
moves.desc: For 5 turns, the user and its party members take 0.5x damage from physical attacks, or 0.66x damage if in a Double Battle. Damage is not reduced further with Aurora Veil. Critical hits ignore this effect. It is removed from the user's side if the user or an ally is successfully hit by Brick Break, Psychic Fangs, or Defog. Lasts for 8 turns if the user is holding Light Clay. Fails if the effect is already active on the user's side.
moves.shortDesc: For 5 turns, physical damage to allies is halved.

moves.name: Brick Break
moves.desc: If this attack does not miss, the effects of Reflect, Light Screen, and Aurora Veil end for the target's side of the field before damage is calculated.
moves.shortDesc: Destroys screens, unless the target is immune.

moves.name: Draining Kiss
moves.desc: The user recovers 3/4 the HP lost by the target, rounded half up. If Big Root is held by the user, the HP recovered is 1.3x normal, rounded half down.
moves.shortDesc: User recovers 75% of the damage dealt.

moves.name: Grass Knot
moves.desc: This move's power is 20 if the target weighs less than 10 kg, 40 if less than 25 kg, 60 if less than 50 kg, 80 if less than 100 kg, 100 if less than 200 kg, and 120 if greater than or equal to 200 kg.
moves.shortDesc: More power the heavier the target.

moves.name: Knock Off
moves.desc: If the target is holding an item that can be removed from it, ignoring the Sticky Hold Ability, this move's power is multiplied by 1.5. If the user has not fainted, the target loses its held item. This move cannot cause Pokemon with the Sticky Hold Ability to lose their held item or cause a Kyogre, a Groudon, a Giratina, an Arceus, a Genesect, a Silvally, a Zacian, or a Zamazenta to lose their Blue Orb, Red Orb, Griseous Orb, Plate, Drive, Memory, Rusted Sword, or Rusted Shield respectively. Items lost to this move cannot be regained with Recycle or the Harvest Ability.
moves.shortDesc: 1.5x damage if foe holds an item. Removes item.

moves.name: Eerie Impulse
moves.desc: Lowers the target's Special Attack by 2 stages.
moves.shortDesc: Lowers the target's Sp. Atk by 2.

moves.name: Electric Terrain
moves.desc: For 5 turns, the terrain becomes Electric Terrain. During the effect, the power of Electric-type attacks made by grounded Pokemon is multiplied by 1.3 and grounded Pokemon cannot fall asleep; Pokemon already asleep do not wake up. Grounded Pokemon cannot become affected by Yawn or fall asleep from its effect. Camouflage transforms the user into an Electric type, Nature Power becomes Thunderbolt, and Secret Power has a 30% chance to cause paralysis. Fails if the current terrain is Electric Terrain.
moves.shortDesc: 5 turns. Grounded: +Electric power, can't sleep.

moves.name: Fake Tears
moves.desc: Lowers the target's Special Defense by 2 stages.
moves.shortDesc: Lowers the target's Sp. Def by 2.

moves.name: Wish
moves.desc: At the end of the next turn, the Pokemon at the user's position has 1/2 of the user's maximum HP restored to it, rounded down. Fails if this move is already in effect for the user's position.
moves.shortDesc: Next turn, 50% of the user's max HP is restored.

moves.name: Discharge
moves.desc: Has a 30% chance to paralyze the target.
moves.shortDesc: 30% chance to paralyze adjacent Pokemon.

moves.name: Play Nice
moves.desc: Lowers the target's Attack by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: Lowers the target's Attack by 1.

moves.name: Charm
moves.desc: Lowers the target's Attack by 2 stages.
moves.shortDesc: Lowers the target's Attack by 2.

moves.name: Rain Dance
moves.desc: For 5 turns, the weather becomes Rain Dance. The damage of Water-type attacks is multiplied by 1.5 and the damage of Fire-type attacks is multiplied by 0.5 during the effect. Lasts for 8 turns if the user is holding Damp Rock. Fails if the current weather is Rain Dance.
moves.shortDesc: For 5 turns, heavy rain powers Water moves.

moves.name: Light Screen
moves.desc: For 5 turns, the user and its party members take 0.5x damage from special attacks, or 0.66x damage if in a Double Battle. Damage is not reduced further with Aurora Veil. Critical hits ignore this effect. It is removed from the user's side if the user or an ally is successfully hit by Brick Break, Psychic Fangs, or Defog. Lasts for 8 turns if the user is holding Light Clay. Fails if the effect is already active on the user's side.
moves.shortDesc: For 5 turns, special damage to allies is halved.

moves.name: Focus Blast
moves.desc: Has a 10% chance to lower the target's Special Defense by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 10% chance to lower the target's Sp. Def by 1.

moves.name: Volt Tackle
moves.desc: Has a 10% chance to paralyze the target. If the target lost HP, the user takes recoil damage equal to 33% the HP lost by the target, rounded half up, but not less than 1 HP.
moves.shortDesc: Has 33% recoil. 10% chance to paralyze target.

moves.name: Thief
moves.desc: If this attack was successful and the user has not fainted, it steals the target's held item if the user is not holding one. The target's item is not stolen if it is a Mail or Z-Crystal, or if the target is a Kyogre holding a Blue Orb, a Groudon holding a Red Orb, a Giratina holding a Griseous Orb, an Arceus holding a Plate, a Genesect holding a Drive, a Silvally holding a Memory, or a Pokemon that can Mega Evolve holding the Mega Stone for its species. Items lost to this move cannot be regained with Recycle or the Harvest Ability.
moves.shortDesc: If the user has no item, it steals the target's.

moves.name: Tickle
moves.desc: Lowers the target's Attack and Defense by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: Lowers the target's Attack and Defense by 1.

moves.name: Quick Attack
moves.desc: No additional effect.
moves.shortDesc: Usually goes first.

moves.name: Play Rough
moves.desc: Has a 10% chance to lower the target's Attack by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 10% chance to lower the target's Attack by 1.

moves.name: Fly
moves.desc: This attack charges on the first turn and executes on the second. On the first turn, the user avoids all attacks other than Gust, Hurricane, Sky Uppercut, Smack Down, Thousand Arrows, Thunder, and Twister, and Gust and Twister have doubled power when used against it. If the user is holding a Power Herb, the move completes in one turn.
moves.shortDesc: Flies up on first turn, then strikes the next turn.

moves.name: Nasty Plot
moves.desc: Raises the user's Special Attack by 2 stages.
moves.shortDesc: Raises the user's Sp. Atk by 2.

moves.name: Fling
moves.desc: The power of this move is based on the user's held item. The held item is lost and it activates for the target if applicable. If there is no target or the target avoids this move by protecting itself, the user's held item is still lost. The user can regain a thrown item with Recycle or the Harvest Ability. Fails if the user has no held item, if the held item cannot be thrown, if the user is under the effect of Embargo or Magic Room, or if the user has the Klutz Ability.
moves.shortDesc: Flings the user's item at the target. Power varies.

moves.name: Iron Tail
moves.desc: Has a 30% chance to lower the target's Defense by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 30% chance to lower the target's Defense by 1.

moves.name: Focus Punch
moves.desc: The user loses its focus and does nothing if it is hit by a damaging attack this turn before it can execute the move.
moves.shortDesc: Fails if the user takes damage before it hits.

moves.name: Reversal
moves.desc: The power of this move is 20 if X is 33 to 48, 40 if X is 17 to 32, 80 if X is 10 to 16, 100 if X is 5 to 9, 150 if X is 2 to 4, and 200 if X is 0 or 1, where X is equal to (user's current HP * 48 / user's maximum HP), rounded down.
moves.shortDesc: More power the less HP the user has left.

moves.name: Dig
moves.desc: This attack charges on the first turn and executes on the second. On the first turn, the user avoids all attacks other than Earthquake and Magnitude but takes double damage from them, and is also unaffected by weather. If the user is holding a Power Herb, the move completes in one turn.
moves.shortDesc: Digs underground turn 1, strikes turn 2.

moves.name: Electro Ball
moves.desc: The power of this move depends on (user's current Speed / target's current Speed), rounded down. Power is equal to 150 if the result is 4 or more, 120 if 3, 80 if 2, 60 if 1, 40 if less than 1. If the target's current Speed is 0, this move's power is 40.
moves.shortDesc: More power the faster the user is than the target.

moves.name: Thunder Punch
moves.desc: Has a 10% chance to paralyze the target.
moves.shortDesc: 10% chance to paralyze the target.

moves.name: Trailblaze
moves.desc: Has a 100% chance to raise the user's Speed by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 100% chance to raise the user's Speed by 1.

moves.name: Substitute
moves.desc: The user takes 1/4 of its maximum HP, rounded down, and puts it into a substitute to take its place in battle. The substitute is removed once enough damage is inflicted on it, or if the user switches out or faints. Baton Pass can be used to transfer the substitute to an ally, and the substitute will keep its remaining HP. Until the substitute is broken, it receives damage from all attacks made by other Pokemon and shields the user from status effects and stat stage changes caused by other Pokemon. Sound-based moves and Pokemon with the Infiltrator Ability ignore substitutes. The user still takes normal damage from weather and status effects while behind its substitute. If the substitute breaks during a multi-hit attack, the user will take damage from any remaining hits. If a substitute is created while the user is trapped by a binding move, the binding effect ends immediately. Fails if the user does not have enough HP remaining to create a substitute without fainting, or if it already has a substitute.
moves.shortDesc: User takes 1/4 its max HP to put in a substitute.

moves.name: Hyper Beam
moves.desc: If this move is successful, the user must recharge on the following turn and cannot select a move.
moves.shortDesc: User cannot move next turn.

moves.name: Wild Charge
moves.desc: If the target lost HP, the user takes recoil damage equal to 1/4 the HP lost by the target, rounded half up, but not less than 1 HP.
moves.shortDesc: Has 1/4 recoil.

moves.name: Agility
moves.desc: Raises the user's Speed by 2 stages.
moves.shortDesc: Raises the user's Speed by 2.

moves.name: Endure
moves.desc: The user will survive attacks made by other Pokemon during this turn with at least 1 HP. This move has a 1/X chance of being successful, where X starts at 1 and triples each time this move is successfully used. X resets to 1 if this move fails, if the user's last move used is not Baneful Bunker, Burning Bulwark, Detect, Endure, King's Shield, Max Guard, Obstruct, Protect, Quick Guard, Silk Trap, Spiky Shield, or Wide Guard, or if it was one of those moves and the user's protection was broken. Fails if the user moves last this turn.
moves.shortDesc: User survives attacks this turn with at least 1 HP.

moves.name: Sleep Talk
moves.desc: One of the user's known moves, besides this move, is selected for use at random. Fails if the user is not asleep. The selected move does not have PP deducted from it, and can currently have 0 PP. This move cannot select Assist, Beak Blast, Belch, Bide, Blazing Torque, Celebrate, Chatter, Combat Torque, Copycat, Dynamax Cannon, Focus Punch, Hold Hands, Magical Torque, Me First, Metronome, Mimic, Mirror Move, Nature Power, Noxious Torque, Shell Trap, Sketch, Sleep Talk, Struggle, Uproar, Wicked Torque, or any two-turn move.
moves.shortDesc: User must be asleep. Uses another known move.

moves.name: Charge Beam
moves.desc: Has a 70% chance to raise the user's Special Attack by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 70% chance to raise the user's Sp. Atk by 1.

moves.name: Charge
moves.desc: Raises the user's Special Defense by 1 stage. The user's next Electric-type attack will have its power doubled; the effect ends when the user is no longer active, or after the user attempts to use any Electric-type move besides Charge, even if it is not successful.
moves.shortDesc: +1 SpD, user's next Electric move 2x power.

moves.name: Present
moves.desc: If this move is successful, it deals damage or heals the target. 40% chance for 40 power, 30% chance for 80 power, 10% chance for 120 power, and 20% chance to heal the target by 1/4 of its maximum HP, rounded down.
moves.shortDesc: 40, 80, 120 power, or heals target 1/4 max HP.

abilities.name: Lightning Rod
abilities.desc: This Pokemon is immune to Electric-type moves and raises its Special Attack by 1 stage when hit by an Electric-type move. If this Pokemon is not the target of a single-target Electric-type move used by another Pokemon, this Pokemon redirects that move to itself if it is within the range of that move. If multiple Pokemon could redirect with this Ability, it goes to the one with the highest Speed, or in the case of a tie to the one that has had this Ability active longer.
abilities.shortDesc: This Pokemon draws Electric moves to itself to raise Sp. Atk by 1; Electric immunity.

abilities.name: Static
abilities.desc: 30% chance a Pokemon making contact with this Pokemon will be paralyzed.
abilities.shortDesc: 30% chance a Pokemon making contact with this Pokemon will be paralyzed.

items.name: Focus Sash
items.desc: If holder's HP is full, will survive an attack that would KO it with 1 HP. Single use.

items.name: Assault Vest
items.desc: Holder's Sp. Def is 1.5x, but it can only select damaging moves.

items.name: Covert Cloak
items.desc: Holder is not affected by the secondary effect of another Pokemon's attack.

items.name: Sitrus Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/4 max HP when at 1/2 max HP or less. Single use.

items.name: Life Orb
items.desc: Holder's attacks do 1.3x damage, and it loses 1/10 its max HP after the attack.

items.name: Leftovers
items.desc: At the end of every turn, holder restores 1/16 of its max HP.

items.name: Safety Goggles
items.desc: Holder is immune to powder moves and damage from Sandstorm or Hail.

items.name: Air Balloon
items.desc: Holder is immune to Ground-type attacks. Pops when holder is hit.

items.name: Magnet
items.desc: Holder's Electric-type attacks have 1.2x power.

items.name: Light Clay

items.name: Absorb Bulb
items.desc: Raises holder's Sp. Atk by 1 stage if hit by a Water-type attack. Single use.

items.name: Shuca Berry
items.desc: Halves damage taken from a supereffective Ground-type attack. Single use.

items.name: Electric Seed
items.desc: If the terrain is Electric Terrain, raises holder's Defense by 1 stage. Single use.

items.name: Aguav Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/3 max HP at 1/4 max HP or less; confuses if -SpD Nature. Single use.

items.name: Expert Belt
items.desc: Holder's attacks that are super effective against the target do 1.2x damage.

items.name: Choice Scarf
items.desc: Holder's Speed is 1.5x, but it can only select the first move it executes.

items.name: Wiki Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/3 max HP at 1/4 max HP or less; confuses if -SpA Nature. Single use.

items.name: Heavy-Duty Boots
items.desc: When switching in, the holder is unaffected by hazards on its side of the field.

items.name: Mago Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/3 max HP at 1/4 max HP or less; confuses if -Spe Nature. Single use.

items.name: Eject Button
items.desc: If holder survives a hit, it immediately switches out to a chosen ally. Single use.

items.name: Salac Berry
items.desc: Raises holder's Speed by 1 stage when at 1/4 max HP or less. Single use.

items.name: Light Ball
items.desc: If held by a Pikachu, its Attack and Sp. Atk are doubled.

items.name: Shell Bell
items.desc: After an attack, holder gains 1/8 of the damage in HP dealt to other Pokemon.

items.name: Rocky Helmet
items.desc: If holder is hit by a contact move, the attacker loses 1/6 of its max HP.

items.name: Red Card
items.desc: If holder survives a hit, attacker is forced to switch to a random ally. Single use.

items.name: King's Rock
items.desc: Holder's attacks without a chance to make the target flinch gain a 10% chance to make the target flinch. Evolves Poliwhirl into Politoed and Slowpoke into Slowking when traded.

items.name: Choice Specs
items.desc: Holder's Sp. Atk is 1.5x, but it can only select the first move it executes.

items.name: Iapapa Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/3 max HP at 1/4 max HP or less; confuses if -Def Nature. Single use.

items.name: Quick Claw
items.desc: Each turn, holder has a 20% chance to move first in its priority bracket.

items.name: Zap Plate
items.desc: Holder's Electric-type attacks have 1.2x power. Judgment is Electric type.

items.name: Damp Rock
items.desc: Holder's use of Rain Dance lasts 8 turns instead of 5.

items.name: Eviolite
items.desc: If holder's species can evolve, its Defense and Sp. Def are 1.5x.

items.name: Bright Powder
items.desc: The accuracy of attacks against the holder is 0.9x.

items.name: Mystic Water
items.desc: Holder's Water-type attacks have 1.2x power.

items.name: Mental Herb
items.desc: Cures holder of Attract, Disable, Encore, Heal Block, Taunt, Torment. Single use.

items.name: Mirror Herb
items.desc: When an opposing Pokemon raises a stat stage, the holder copies it. Single use.

items.name: Focus Band
items.desc: Holder has a 10% chance to survive an attack that would KO it with 1 HP.

items.name: Figy Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/3 max HP at 1/4 max HP or less; confuses if -Atk Nature. Single use.

items.name: Clear Amulet
items.desc: Prevents other Pokemon from lowering the holder's stat stages.

items.name: Scope Lens
items.desc: Holder's critical hit ratio is raised by 1 stage.

items.name: Rindo Berry
items.desc: Halves damage taken from a supereffective Grass-type attack. Single use.

items.name: Muscle Band
items.desc: Holder's physical attacks have 1.1x power.

items.name: Choice Band
items.desc: Holder's Attack is 1.5x, but it can only select the first move it executes.

items.name: Wide Lens
items.desc: The accuracy of attacks by the holder is 1.1x.

items.name: Soft Sand
items.desc: Holder's Ground-type attacks have 1.2x power.

items.name: Metronome
items.desc: Damage of moves used on consecutive turns is increased. Max 2x after 5 turns.

items.name: Fairy Feather
items.desc: Holder's Fairy-type attacks have 1.2x power.

items.name: Wise Glasses
items.desc: Holder's special attacks have 1.1x power.

items.name: Lum Berry
items.desc: Holder cures itself if it has a non-volatile status or is confused. Single use.

items.name: Room Service
items.desc: If Trick Room is active, the holder's Speed is lowered by 1 stage. Single use.
